[{"question":"Why are you so critical of the president\u0027s actions so far in relation to Syria?","answer":"Well, first of all, we have watched the Syria evolve into one of the great humanitarian tragedies in recent history.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":34,"aSentId":35},{"question":"How did you get around that?","answer":"Well, first of all I think it\u0027s understandable that Americans are very skeptical and cynical and that\u0027s why the actions that we should have been taking and should still be taking have to be explained to the American people and the consequences of widespread conflict -- regional conflict in the Middle East.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":53,"aSentId":54},{"question":"Is that the position you take in?","answer":"I\u0027ve only taken it for two years, that\u0027s fairly well- known and the fact is when we haven\u0027t the situation has deteriorated in the numbers and the tragedies that I just described to you have taken place.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":128,"aSentId":129},{"question":"What is your reaction?","answer":"Well, I think that we do have a situation, what that calls for some very, very serious consideration for -- of our options.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":141,"aSentId":142},{"question":"Is it America\u0027s place anymore in the modern world now to be getting involved in other country\u0027s civil wars?","answer":"Well, I think it\u0027s America\u0027s place to show leadership in resolving some of these very, very difficult and dangerous situations and you do that in a number of ways.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":155,"aSentId":156},{"question":"General Hayden the problem is no one\u0027s quite sure what the plan is and President Obama hasn\u0027t committed yet to what the plan may be and that plan may now have to dramatically change if British forces will not be involved and that sets a bandwagon running around say, the French and other internal forces he said, \"Look, we just can\u0027t take part in this,\" would America consider unilateral military action under those circumstances and how risky is that to America\u0027s interest?","answer":"No, I think the United States would act unilaterally because President Obama made this commitment for the United States and frankly for himself personally about a year ago.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":194,"aSentId":195},{"question":"What does that lead him politically and what would you think is the sensible course of action now?","answer":"Well, this is an enormous set back for the Administration.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":201,"aSentId":202},{"question":"How dangerous would that be?","answer":"It\u0027s quite dangerous and it\u0027s a separable choice from responding appropriately to what Assad has done with chemical weapons.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":242,"aSentId":243},{"question":"But if you are President Obama, what do you do and how soon do you do it?","answer":"Well this is the problem, I mean he\u0027s going to the G20 group of industrialized nations and for major consultations leaving Tuesday night.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":249,"aSentId":250},{"question":"Why do we fear them so much?","answer":"I mean chemical weapons there\u0027s all sorts of different types of them, but in this particular case, you\u0027re right we\u0027re talking about something let\u0027s say, particularly chilling these neurotoxic agents and in this case the belief is that sarin which is probably one of the most toxic chemical weapons out there that\u0027s been used in warfare is what they suspect it is and this is something they can test for pretty easily up here.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"And Sanjay, from all of the video evidence that you\u0027ve seen some awful images of young kids being slaughtered and so on, does it look to you like the side effects of a sarin attack or something very similar?","answer":"I think so, you know, it\u0027s tough to sometimes make, you know, make conclusions from that video evidence alone, but hearing some of the doctors\u0027 descriptions of these in some of these camps and the doctors without boarders over there.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":278,"aSentId":279},{"question":"Are they sensible to try and do what they\u0027re doing?","answer":"No, and you know, Piers it\u0027s sad actually to watch that because I mean I -- people think -- they may think that they\u0027re protecting themselves in some way and it\u0027s sad because maybe that\u0027s the only thing that they have.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":301,"aSentId":302},{"question":"What do you think of what she said?","answer":"It was rather astonishing and I gratefully spoke with you about this once already.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":339,"aSentId":340},{"question":"Is there anything wrong inherently about her behavior?","answer":"Right.","docId":"130829pmt","qSentId":408,"aSentId":409}]